# Key Takeaway

This lab demonstrates that even when an application returns generic authentication error messages, subtle differences in server responses can still reveal valid usernames. Burp Suite Intruder's **Grep - Match** feature helps identify these inconsistencies efficiently, enabling attackers to enumerate accounts before launching password attacks. Eliminating response differences and implementing robust authentication controls are essential to mitigating this vulnerability.
